# __MODULE_NAME__

A [SovEcom](https://github.com/) module, scaffolded with `create-sovecom-module`.

## What's here

```
__MODULE_NAME__/
├── sovecom.module.json   # the manifest: name, version, compatibleCore, permissions, slots, tables
├── package.json          # depends on @sovecom/module-sdk; builds to a CJS dist/index.js
├── tsconfig.json         # emits CommonJS (the worker loader requires a CJS entry)
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts          # the module body — `defineModule({ activate(sdk) { ... } })`
│   └── db/
│       └── schema.ts      # namespaced `mod___MODULE_NAME___*` table declarations
├── README.md
├── .gitignore
└── LICENSE               # AGPL-3.0
```

## The module contract

A module is a single `activate(sdk)` body run inside a sandboxed worker. `sdk` is the capability
object — your only channel to core:

| Capability   | Permission needed   | What it does                                              |
| ------------ | ------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `sdk.store`  | `read:products`, …  | Read the storefront catalog (gated, field-limited).      |
| `sdk.admin`  | `read:orders`, …    | Read admin data (gated, field-limited; no raw PII).      |
| `sdk.tables` | `write:own_tables`  | Parameterized SQL against your OWN `mod_<name>_*` tables. |
| `sdk.events` | `subscribe:events`, `emit:events` | Subscribe to / emit domain events.          |
| `sdk.http`   | `http:outbound`     | Mediated, SSRF-guarded outbound HTTP.                    |
| `sdk.serve`  | (none)              | Mount one HTTP handler under your module's routes.        |

Declare the **minimum** permissions in `sovecom.module.json`. Core enforces them; the SDK cannot
widen them. Slots are **declarative manifest metadata** — there is no runtime `registerSlot()`.

## Develop

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm build      # tsc → dist/index.js (CommonJS, exports activate)
```

The built `dist/index.js` is what the SovEcom runtime loads (`SOVECOM_MODULE_MAIN=<dir>/index.js`).

